title: Syrian refugee elected mayor of German town, years after fleeing war
description: A Syrian who arrived in Germany as a refugee in 2015 has won a mayoral election in the southwestern German state of Baden-Württemberg.

title: Amsterdam Schiphol Airport proposes a ban on private jets
description: High flyers hoping to hop to the Netherlands in a private jet might be forced to rethink their travel plans, as Amsterdam's Schiphol Airport is proposing a private jet ban.

title: India avalanche kills six, injures 17
description: Six tourists were killed and 17 others injured in a major avalanche in India's northeastern state of Sikkim, local police said Tuesday.

title: Around the world, criminal charges are no barrier to high office
description: Donald Trump may be the first former US president to face criminal charges, but around the world many current and former leaders have been prosecuted or even spent time in jail.

title: One killed and 30 injured in train accident near The Hague
description: At least one person was killed and 30 injured, many seriously, when a passenger train carrying about 50 people derailed in the Netherlands early Tuesday after hitting construction equipment on the track, Dutch emergency services said.

title: Australia bans TikTok on federal government devices
description: Australia has joined other countries in banning the use of TikTok on devices used by federal departments and agencies.

title: Malaysia scraps mandatory death penalty, natural-life prison terms
description: Malaysia's parliament on Monday passed sweeping legal reforms to remove the mandatory death penalty, trim the number of offenses punishable by death, and abolish natural-life prison sentences, a move cautiously welcomed by rights groups.
